QUERY:  risk factors for prostate cancer trans man
DATE: 01-29-2025
Risk factors for prostate cancer in trans men include hormone therapy, family history, and age at which they transition. [1, 2, 3]
Hormone therapy [1]
Taking testosterone can increase the risk of prostate cancer. [1]
Taking feminizing hormones like estrogen or testosterone blockers can reduce the risk. [3]
Hormone therapy can lower PSA levels, which may make it harder to detect prostate cancer. [4]
Family history [3]
Having a family history of prostate cancer increases the risk. [3]
Genes are passed down from parents and can increase the risk of cancer. [5]
Age at transition [3]
Starting hormone therapy later in life may increase the risk.
Other risk factors [6, 7]
Chronic inflammation, which can be caused by infections, radiation, hormones, and chemicals
Smoking
Obesity
Lack of cancer screening
Symptoms [8]
Frequent urination, especially at night
Painful or burning urination
Blood in urine or semen
Difficulty getting an erection
Pain in the lower back, hips, chest, thighs, or pelvis
If you experience any new, unexplained, or changing symptoms, you should speak with your doctor. [8]


